{{Quote|You... ''you'' are the darkness! Iziz will fall. It cannot withstand the pressure of this heavy shadow for much longer.|Olis to [[Queen/Legends|Queen]] [[Amanoa]]|<ref name="Tales of the Jedi Companion">''[[Tales of the Jedi Companion]]''</ref>}}
'''Olis''' was a male Human prisoner of the city [[Iziz/Legends|Iziz]] on [[Onderon/Legends|Onderon]] around [[4000 BBY/Legends|4000 BBY]]. Olis was to be cast out to the wild outside Iziz as punishment. Before [[Queen/Legends|Queen]] [[Amanoa]] finalized the punishment, Olis foretold that Iziz would fall due to its suffering from the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|darkness]] for three centuries. He might be a [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]], as he claimed to be able to sense the dark side in the Queen.

Olis's words enraged the Queen, and Amanoa executed the prisoner with a glowing sphere of energy in green. After the body of Olis was removed from the throne room, [[Ulic Qel-Droma/Legends|Ulic Qel-Droma]] and his [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] companion entered to negotiate about the [[Beast Wars]].

